              "free_text": [
                "",
                "A self supporting natural indium target with 95.7%",
                " isotopic abundance of 115In was used. The target",
                " thickness was measured by alpha energy loss method to",
                " be 220 ug/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two telescopes with surface",
                "  barrier silicon detectors were set up two movable",
                "  arms inside a 1 m diam. scattering chamber for",
                "  determination of charge, mass and energy of the",
                "  ejectiles.",
                " The telescopes employed 15-30 um thick dE detectors",
                "  and 300 um thick E detectors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Another silicon detector of 300 um thickness was",
                " placed at a forward angle to monitor the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
